Customer Service










Home / About Us / AEP Websites





Social Media





AEP Web Sites
Customer Service Sites

                Customers of AEP's public utilities may pay their bills online, view their usage
        history, and perform other tasks at the following sites:
            


AEP Ohio - AEP Ohio
            serves 1.4 million customers in Ohio and the northern panhandle of West Virginia.
            http://www.AEPOhio.com

AEP Texas - AEP Texas
            serves more than 900,000 electric consumers in the deregulated Texas marketplace.
            http://www.AEPTexas.com

Appalachian Power - Appalachian Power serves 929,000 customers in West Virginia, Virginia, and
            Tennessee. http://www.AppalachianPower.com

Indiana Michigan Power
                    - Indiana Michigan Power serves 589,000 customers in Indiana and Michigan. http://www.IndianaMichiganPower.com

Kentucky Power
                    - Kentucky Power serves approximately 175,000 customers in eastern Kentucky. http://www.KentuckyPower.com

PSO - Public Service
            Company of Oklahoma serves 505,000 customers in Oklahoma. http://www.PSOklahoma.com

SWEPCO - Southwestern
            Electric Power Company serves 520,400 customers in Louisiana, Arkansas, East Texas
            and the Panhandle area of North Texas. http://www.SWEPCO.com


AEP National Accounts
                customers can find customer service online at http://www.AEPNationalAccounts.com

Retail Electrical Supply
AEP Energy - AEP Energy was created in 2002 as a competitive retail electric supply affiliate of American Electric Power (AEP). We are committed to excellence by serving Ohio businesses with our leadership, innovation and many years of Industry experience.
Wind Farms

Desert Sky Wind Farm - The Desert Sky Wind Farm is a 160.5-megawatt wind power generation facility located near the far West Texas town of Iraan, in Pecos County. The site includes 107 turbines, each rated at 1.5 megawatts  spread over a 15-square-mile area on Indian Mesa.
                
http://www.desertskywind.com


Trent Mesa Wind Farm - Trent Mesa Wind Farm is a 150-megawatt wind power plant located between Abilene and Sweetwater in West Texas. The project uses 100 turbines each rated at 1.5 megawatts.
                
http://www.trentmesa.com 

Hydro Projects

Claytor Hydroelectric Project - The Claytor Hydroelectric Project, owned and operated by Appalachian Power Company, is licensed by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC) as Project No. 739.The Claytor Project consists of a concrete gravity dam with gated spillway, integral intake and powerhouse, switching equipment, appurtenant facilities and the reservoir.
                
http://www.claytorhydro.com


Kanawha Hydro Projects - Appalachian Power is seeking to relicense the London/Marmet and Winfield hydroelectric projects, in consultation with representatives from various State and Federal agencies as well as local governments, non-governmental organizations and the public.
                
http://www.kanawhahydro.com


Smith Mountain Project - Smith Mountain is a pumped storage project that utilizes an upper reservoir (Smith Mountain Lake) and a lower reservoir (Leesville Lake.)
                
http://www.smithmtn.com

Other AEP sites

AEP Economic Development -  AEP's professional economic development staff works strategically with many organizations, communities and allies to provide smart and effective business opportunities to both prospective and existing businesses and industries. We provide information on available sites and buildings, along with community profiles and many years of experience in the communities we serve. We also provide turnkey engineering, construction, procurement, and maintenance services to commercial and industrial customers, electric cooperatives, and municipal utilities.
http://www.aeped.com


AEP Electronic Data Interchange
                - Organizations that exchange business documents (such as invoices or purchase orders)
        via paper with AEP can increase the reliability of those transactions while decreasing
        business costs through Electronic Data Interchange, or EDI.
http://www.AEPedi.com


AEP Surplus
                - AEP offers prospective buyers an opportunity to buy or bid on obsolete,
        used, or excess equipment and materials from various sites within our operating territory.
http://www.aepsurplus.com/


AEP Sustainability
                - AEP's Corporate Sustainability website. Developed to allow for more comprehenseive
integrated reporting on our total performance. We report using the Global Reporting Initiative (GRI) protocol and our report is checked by GRI.
http://www.AEPsustainability.com


Dolan Technology Center - AEP's Dolan Technology Center offers a staff of flexible, resourceful experts in instrumentation development/implementation, test formulation/implementation, and  technical support. Dolan Technology Center brings to your project expertise gained from the long history and vast knowledge of supporting AEP's distribution, transmission and generation companies, along with a keen focus on new electrotechnology developments.
                
http://www.dolantechcenter.com/


United Sciences Testing,
           Inc. - USTI performs plant emissions flow monitoring, employing
        an automated process that eliminates or significantly reduces over-reporting of
        emissions, thereby saving time and money.
http://www.ustirata.com

Joint Transmission Projects

Electric Transmission Texas - Electric Transmission Texas, LLC (ETT) is a joint venture between AEP  and MidAmerican Energy Holdings Company, which will build transmission projects within the Electric Reliability Council of Texas (ERCOT).
    
http://www.ettexas.com


Pioneer Transmission - Pioneer Transmission, LLC is a joint venture formed by Duke Energy and American Electric Power (AEP) to build and operate 240 miles of extra-high-voltage 765-kilovolt (kV) transmission lines and related facilities in Indiana.
http://www.pnrtransmission.com/


RITE Line Transmission - Reliability Interregional Transmission Extension or RITE Line is a joint venture formed by Exelon Corporation and Electric Transmission America (ETA) - a joint venture of subsidiaries of American Electric Power and MidAmerican Energy holdings - to build and operate approximately 420 miles of high-voltage transmission lines and related facilities in Indiana and Illinois.
http://www.ritelinetransco.com/


Transource Energy - Transource, a partnership between AEP and Great Plains Energy, is dedicated to investing in and building new electric transmission infrastructure in a competitive marketplace. The focus of Transource is the development of cost-effective transmission solutions, initially within the PJM Interconnection, Southwest Power Pool (SPP) and the Midwest Independent System Operator (MISO) regions.
http://www.transourceenergy.com/

Employee & Retiree Sites
AEPnow.com (Employees only)  - AEP Now is the official corporate intranet (internal Web site) at AEP, offering corporate news and other information for employees; AEPnow.com enables remote access to AEP Now and HR Now.

AEPretirees.com - The official Web site dedicated to serving retirees and other alumni of American Electric Power providing relevant news and announcements from AEP; updates about the people who have served AEP; and links to other related Web sites.








Customer Service
Join our conversations on Twitter and Facebook. Learn more about us through YouTube and Flickr.

                American Electric Power delivers electricity
        to approximately five million residential, commercial and industrial customers in
        the United States. Our service territory includes portions of Arkansas, Indiana,
        Kentucky, Louisiana, Michigan, Ohio, Oklahoma, Tennessee, Texas, Virginia, and West
        Virginia
            








